Reasoning: The paper deals with channel code design for a communication system with side information at the encoder. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of side information also relates to the field of source coding and data compression (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the design of codes for binary symmetric channels, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.DS). Finally, the use of interference in the channel model may also relate to the field of network information theory (cs.NI).
